{{Infobox book | name=A Mão e a Luva | image = Luiz Alberto Pinheiro de Freitas - Freud e Machado de Assis uma interseção entre psicanálise e literatura.jpeg | author=[[Machado de Assis]] | language= [[Brazilian Portuguese]] | country= [[Brazil]] | pub_date= 1874 | pages= 160 | isbn=978-85-380-0351-9 }} '''''A Mão e a Luva''''' (''The Hand and the Glove'') is a [[romance novel]] written by [[Brazil]]ian author [[Machado de Assis]] (1839–1908) and published in 1874. The [[book]] is a [[psychology|psychological]] analysis of [[society]] and of ''false [[naivety]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.machadodeassis.net/hiperTx_romances/obras/amaoealuva.htm |title=A Mão e a Luva |publisher=machadodeassis.net |accessdate=16 March 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100710054951/http://www.machadodeassis.net/hiperTx_romances/obras/amaoealuva.htm |archivedate=10 July 2010 }}</ref>
== Story == The story revolves around Guiomar,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mundovestibular.com.br/articles/435/1/A-MAO-E-A-LUVA---Machado-De-Assis-Resumo/Paacutegina1.html|title=A Mão e a Luva – Machado de Assis, Resumo|publisher=Mundo Vestibular|accessdate=16 March 2012}}</ref> a 17-year-old girl, goddaughter to a [[baron]]ess. Guiomar wishes to raise her [[social position]] and is sought after by three men: Jorge, Estêvão and Luís Alves. Estêvão loves her crazily, purely and innocently – she is his first love. Jorge, nephew to the baroness and her obvious favorite, sees Guiomar as a path to ''social climbing'',<ref>{{cite book|title=Freud e Machado de Assis, uma Interseção entre Psicanálise e Literatura|page=63|last=Freitas|first=Luís Alberto Pinheiro de|publisher=Mauad|place=Rio de Janeiro|edition=2|year=2001|isbn=978-85-7478-056-6}}</ref> and has "a lustful kind of love", as described by the author. Luís Alves is a middle-term: his intentions are of an ambitious nature, but throughout the book he gradually becomes fond of Guiomar.
Jorge, with the support of the baroness and her British maid, Mrs. Oswald, requests Guiomar's hand in marriage. On the following day, Luís Alves asks as well. The baroness leaves the decision in Guiomar's hands, and, between the two admirers, she chooses Jorge, but the baroness knows she actually wants to marry Luís Alves. She actually marries Luís Alves and the end of the book justifies the title.
