[[File:Government Seal of Bangladesh.svg|thumb|Seal used by the government of Bangladesh]]
The '''Government Seal of Bangladesh''' ({{lang-bn|বাংলাদেশ সরকারের সীল - Bānglādēś sarkārēr sīl}}) used by the [[Cabinet of Bangladesh]]<ref>http://www.bangladesh.gov.bd/index.php?option=com_weblinks&task=ministry&Itemid=152</ref> and the [[Government of Bangladesh]]<ref>http://www.virtualbangladesh.com/state.html</ref> on official documents.
[[File: Bangladeshi Passport Cover.jpg|thumb|The Government Seal inscribed on the front cover of a [[Bangladeshi passport]]]]
One version is used on the cover page of [[Bangladeshi passport]]s.<ref>http://www.dip.gov.bd</ref> 
The Seal features the same design elements as the first [[Flag of Bangladesh]] in a circular setting. The outer white ring is shown with the caption of the official name of the Government of the People's Republic of Bangladesh in [[Bengali language|Bengali]]: ''গণপ্রজাতন্ত্রী বাংলাদেশ সরকার'' with 4 red 5-pointed stars. In centre the country map on a red disc.

==History==
The seal was adopted as the [[National Emblem of Bangladesh]] by the [[Provisional Government of the People's Republic of Bangladesh]] popularly known as the '''Mujibnagar Government''', was the [[government in exile]] of [[Bangladesh]] based in [[Kolkata]], [[India]], during the [[Bangladesh Liberation War]]. Formed in early April 1971, the provisional government confirmed the declaration of independence of [[East Pakistan]] made earlier by Bengali nationalist leader [[Sheikh Mujibur Rahman]] on 26 March.

