A '''race clock''' (also called a '''display clock''') is [[sports equipment]] with an [[Fourteen-segment display | alpha numeric display]] that typically shows the elapsed time for a [[Racing|race]] or sporting event.
A race clock may be positioned at the finish line of a race or at various key intermediate locations (split points) so that athletes will know their pace. The display is typically either [[light emitting diode]]s or plastic elements that can be flipped to reveal or hide a surface painted with a bright color. The digits on a race clock vary in sizes from 6 inches to a foot in height.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.raceclock.com/|title=Sports Timing Equipment|accessdate=July 8, 2014}}</ref> The clock can be either a free standing piece of equipment on a tripod or finish truss or can be incorporated into a larger [[scoreboard]] display.
